Many people use &quot;generic&quot; formats like

    &lt;Object type=&quot;Person&quot;&gt;
      &lt;Attribute name=&quot;age&quot; value=&quot;24&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;Attribute name=&quot;hair-color&quot; value=&quot;blue&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/Object&gt;

and in my view it&#39;s a terrible mistake. They forget that XML is already extensible, and you get just as much flexibility by writing

    &lt;Person age=&quot;24&quot; hair-color=&quot;blue&quot;/&gt;

The latter form is easier to generate, easier to process, easier to validate, and is just as easy to extend.

