AppleScript&#39;s `do shell script` command works with a default environment that does not load settings you expect when you work in a shell in terminal. The problem here is that the default directory of this stripped-down shell is &#39;/&#39;, meaning you&#39;re trying to unzip your archive at the root level, and running into permissions issues. You should explicitly point to an output directory with the -d option:

    do shell script &quot;unzip -d /Users/abc/Desktop/ /Users/abc/Desktop/1/2/3/5/abc.zip&quot; 

This will unzip the contents of your file to the desktop.

