I think you should start with the outer most model. In this case the `Chapter`. So to get all chapters from books in X country you can use something like this:

    Chapter::whereHas(&#39;book.library.country&#39;, function($q) use ($slug){
      $q-&gt;where(&#39;slug&#39;, $slug)
    })

If you think how SQL queries are executed, from the inside out, then above query builder will make more sense. The query from closure will be executed first.

