Your issue is with following code, you need to refactor to not mix up your prop names with the component name.

[![problem code][1]][1]

You are mixing up `Product` value in your map function with the component named `Product` and you are also passing it a prop named `Product={Product}`, so at the time of rendering, React dont know what `&lt;Product&gt;` is within the context of the map function as at that time `Product` is actually a value of the current iteration.

You can refactor this as following or whatever fits your needs:

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    { value =&gt; value.products.map(product =&gt; &lt;Product key={product.id} currentProduct={product} /&gt; }

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;


  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/Iotu9.png
